# Weather App
# Overview
This Weather App is a simple web application that allows users to get current weather information for any city. The application uses the OpenWeatherMap API to fetch real-time weather data, including temperature, humidity, wind speed, and weather conditions. The app also displays appropriate weather icons based on the conditions.

# Features
Real-time Weather Data: Get current weather information for any city worldwide.
Weather Icons: Displays icons representing the weather conditions (e.g., clear, clouds, rain).
Error Handling: Displays an error message if the city is not found.
How to Use
Enter a City Name: Type the name of the city in the input box.
Click the Search Button: Press the search button to fetch and display the weather information.
View Weather Data: The app displays the city's name, temperature (in Celsius), humidity, wind speed, and an appropriate weather icon.
Error Handling: If the city is not found, an error message is displayed.



# How to Run

Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/weather-app.git

Navigate to the project directory:

bash

Copy code
cd weather-app

Open index.html in your web browser.

# Setup
API Key: Replace the Apikey variable in the JavaScript file with your own OpenWeatherMap API key.

Weather Icons: Ensure that you have the appropriate weather icons in the images directory.

